‚úÖ *CSS Basics You Should Know* üé®üíª  

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to *style* HTML elements ‚Äî adding colors, spacing, layout, and more.

*1Ô∏è‚É£ CSS Syntax*  
```css
selector {
  property: value;
}
```

*Example:*  
```css
h1 {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 32px;
}
```

*2Ô∏è‚É£ How to Add CSS*  
- *Inline:*  
```html
<p style="color: red;">Hello</p>
```
- *Internal (within HTML):*  
```html
<style>
  p { color: green; }
</style>
```
- *External (best practice):*  
```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
```

*3Ô∏è‚É£ Selectors*  
- `*` ‚Üí All elements  
- `p` ‚Üí All `<p>` tags  
- `.class` ‚Üí Elements with class  
- `#id` ‚Üí Element with specific ID  
```css
#title { color: blue; }
.red-text { color: red; }
```

*4Ô∏è‚É£ Colors & Fonts*  
```css
body {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  color: #333;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}
```

*5Ô∏è‚É£ Box Model*  
Every HTML element is a box:  
*content + padding + border + margin*

*6Ô∏è‚É£ Layout with Flexbox*  
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}
```

*7Ô∏è‚É£ Responsive Design*  
```css
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }
}
```

*8Ô∏è‚É£ Hover Effects*  
```css
button:hover {
  background-color: black;
  color: white;
}
```

*9Ô∏è‚É£ Common Properties*
- `color` ‚Äì Text color  
- `background-color` ‚Äì Background  
- `margin` & `padding` ‚Äì Spacing  
- `border` ‚Äì Border style  
- `width` / `height` ‚Äì Size  
- `text-align` ‚Äì Alignment  

üí° *Tip:* Organize your styles using class names and external CSS files for better scalability.

